    <abstract audience="internal" id="aspace_cc621f14a5befba9c99fbac278845d54">The Morse Chain Company was incorporated in 1898 and manufactured power transmission equipment. Its subsidiaries, the Thomas Morse Aircraft Corporation (founded in 1917), the Peters-Morse Manufacturing Company (founded in 1919), and the Barr-Morse Corporation (founded in 1921, manufactured aircrafts, adding machines, and typewriters, respectively. The collection contains business records documenting the transactions of the Morse Chain Company and its subsidiary companies, dating circa 1915-1975.</abstract>
